# Adolescent Mental Health — Page Layout Standards

All marketing pages in `apps/adolescent-mental-health` must share the same section padding and content width as the homepage and shared marketing components.

## Content container

Import `CONTAINER` from `@/lib/site` — never inline `mx-auto max-w-content`:

```tsx
import { CONTAINER } from "@/lib/site";

<div className={CONTAINER}>{/* section content */}</div>
```

Token: `--width-content: 84.375rem` (1350px) in `globals.css` → `max-w-content`.

**Never use `max-w-7xl`, `max-w-6xl`, `max-w-5xl`, or `max-w-4xl` as the primary section container** — they break alignment with navbar, footer, and `PageSection`.

`max-w-3xl`, `max-w-2xl`, `max-w-xl`, and `max-w-lg` are acceptable only for intentionally narrow inner elements (hero copy, pull quotes, intro paragraphs).

## Section wrapper

Standard marketing sections:

```tsx
<section className="bg-white px-6 py-section lg:px-10">
  <div className={CONTAINER}>{children}</div>
</section>
```

Prefer `PageSection` from `@/components/marketing` when the section matches a simple bg + container pattern.

Background alternation: `bg-white` → `bg-surface` → `bg-dark`.

## Homepage hero (exception)

The homepage hero is full-bleed (background spans viewport). Inner copy stays centered and narrow:

```tsx
<div className="relative z-10 mt-auto w-full px-6 pb-16 pt-24 lg:pb-20">
  <div className="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">{/* h1, CTAs, trust strip */}</div>
</div>
```

Do **not** wrap homepage hero copy in `CONTAINER` — editorial centering is intentional.

## Inner-page heroes

Use `PageHero` from `@/components/marketing` — it wraps content in `CONTAINER` by default.

## Therapy page section hierarchy (avoid bento fatigue)

On Individual / Group / Family therapy pages, use **one visual language per section** — do not stack multiple bento/inset-panel/card-grid blocks back-to-back.

| Order | Component | Layout role | Background |
|-------|-----------|-------------|--------------|
| 1 | Hero | Full-bleed dark photo + glass stat panel (`ProgramHeroSection`) | dark image |
| 2 | Stats band | Simple 4-col divide | white |
| 3 | `TherapyOverviewSection` | Split spotlight panel: 3 icon highlights + image (no stat badge) | surface |
| 4 | `SessionStructureSection` | Horizontal 4-step timeline (icon nodes + short body) | white |
| 5 | `GoodFitSection` | Sidebar + 2-col card grid | white |
| 6 | `ClinicalMethodsSection` | **Only dark inset panel** on the page (chip strip + 2×2 grid) | surface |
| 7 | `IopModalityContextSection` | 3-col modality cards, left-aligned header | dark |
| 8 | `TherapyFaqSection` | Sidebar + full-width accordion panel (no CTAs — final band only) | surface |
| 9 | `TherapyFinalCtaSection` | Unified dark split panel | dark |

**Background rhythm:** dark hero → white stats → surface overview → white sessions → white good fit → surface methods → dark IOP → surface FAQ → dark final CTA.

**Content deduplication:** Session frequency lives in the stats band + IOP context cards (and FAQ answers where relevant). Do not repeat cadence in hero chips, overview highlights, or image stat badges.

**Rules:**
- Reserve glass bento (`lg:grid-cols-[1fr_400px]` multi-cell) for homepage + Virtual IOP / flagship program pages only.
- `SessionStructureSection` and `ClinicalMethodsSection` must **never** share the same dark inset-panel shell on one page.
- Do not add decorative watermark numbers (`03`, `04 Phases`) to every section — use at most on `ClinicalMethodsSection`.

